/* Custom Prompt */
.music-custom-prompt {
    width: 100%;
    height: 50px;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: #e1e1e1;
    font-size: 10px;
    resize: none;
}

.music-custom-prompt:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--accent-primary);
}

/* Music Options */
.music-options {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
}

/* Generate Actions */
.music-generate-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
}

.music-generate-actions .btn {
    flex: 1;
}

/* Identify Result */
.music-identify-result {
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding: 10px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 10px;
    display: none;
}

.music-identify-result.visible {
    display: block;
}

.identify-song-title {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #e1e1e1;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.identify-song-artist {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.identify-song-album,
.identify-song-genres {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 9px;
}

/* Music Library */
.music-library-list {
    max-height: 200px;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

.music-library-empty {
    text-align: center;
    color: #666;
    padding: 20px;
    font-size: 10px;
}

.music-library-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 8px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s;
}

.music-library-item:hover {
    background: #333;
}

.music-library-item-info {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
}

.music-library-item-title {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #e1e1e1;
    font-weight: 500;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

.music-library-item-meta {
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
}

.music-library-item-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
}

.music-library-item-actions .btn {
    padding: 4px 6px;
    font-size: 9px;
}

/* Music Status */
.music-status {
    font-size: 10px;
    padding: 4px 0;
    min-height: 18px;
}

.music-status-info {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
}

.music-status-success {
    color: #28a745;
}

.music-status-error {
    color: #dc3545;
}

/* Music Progress */
.music-progress {
    margin: 10px 0;
}

.music-progress.hidden {
    display: none;
}

.music-progress-bar-container {
    height: 4px;
    background: #333;
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.music-progress-bar {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--accent-primary);
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
}

.music-progress-text {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-align: center;
}

/* Music Variations Panel */
.music-variations-panel {
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 10px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.music-variations-panel.hidden {
    display: none;
}

.music-variations-panel>label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.music-variations-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
}

.music-variation-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 8px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 2px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
}

.music-variation-card:hover {
    border-color: #555;
}

.music-variation-card.selected {
    border-color: var(--accent-primary);
}

.variation-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #e1e1e1;
    min-width: 20px;
}

.variation-desc {
    flex: 1;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
}

.variation-play-btn {
    padding: 4px 8px;
    font-size: 9px;
}

/* Music Preview */
.music-preview {
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 10px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.music-preview.hidden {
    display: none;
}

.music-preview-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.music-preview-header span {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #aaa;
}

#music-audio-player {
    width: 100%;
    height: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.music-preview-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
}

.music-preview-actions .btn {
    flex: 1;
}

/* Music Align Modal */
.music-align-modal,
.music-timeline-modal {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    z-index: 1000;
}

.music-align-modal.hidden,
.music-timeline-modal.hidden {
    display: none;
}

.music-align-content,
.music-timeline-content {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-radius: 8px;
    width: 90%;
    max-width: 280px;
    padding: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
}

.music-align-header,
.music-timeline-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.music-align-header span,
.music-timeline-header span {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #e1e1e1;
}

.music-align-info,
.music-timeline-info {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding: 8px;
    background: var(--bg-panel);
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.music-align-info .info-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.music-align-info .info-label {
    color: #666;
}

.music-align-info .info-value {
    color: #e1e1e1;
}

.music-align-actions,
.music-timeline-actions {
    margin-top: 12px;
}

.music-align-actions .btn,
.music-timeline-actions .btn {
    width: 100%;
}

/* Hidden utility */
.hidden {
    display: none !important;
}

/* Collapsed utility */
.collapsed {
    display: none !important;
}

/* Scrollbar */
::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 6px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    background: var(--bg-panel);
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background: var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 3px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
    background: #555;
}

/* Referral Promo Footer */
.referral-promo {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1), rgba(138, 43, 226, 0.1));
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
    padding: 8px 12px;
    z-index: 100;
}

.referral-promo-content {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 11px;
}

.referral-icon {
    font-size: 14px;
}

.referral-text {
    color: var(--text-muted);
}

.referral-text strong {
    color: #00D4FF;
}

.referral-link {
    color: #00D4FF;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    transition: all 0.2s var(--ease-smooth);
}

.referral-link:hover {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
}

content.text:
Now I can see the issue! Looking at the code, I found **multiple critical UI interaction bugs**:

## **Root Cause Analysis**

### **Bug 1: Options Toggle Logic is Inverted** (line 223 in main.js)
```javascript
const isExpanded = ui.optionsPanel.classList.toggle('collapsed');
ui.optionsToggle.classList.toggle('expanded', !isExpanded);
```

**Problem**: `classList.toggle()` returns `true` if the class was **added**, `false` if **removed**. So when toggling `'collapsed'`:
- If panel becomes collapsed â†’ `toggle()` returns `true` â†’ button gets `expanded: false` âŒ
- If panel becomes expanded â†’ `toggle()` returns `false` â†’ button gets `expanded: true` âŒ

This is **backwards**!

### **Bug 2: Section Toggle Icons Don't Update** (lines 241-253, 259-271, 277-289)
```javascript
toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const isCollapsed = panel.classList.toggle('collapsed');
    const icon = toggle.querySelector('.toggle-icon');
    if (icon) {
        icon.textContent = isCollapsed ? '+' : '-';
    }
});
```

**Problem**: Same issue - `toggle()` returns `true` when class is **added** (panel becomes collapsed), but the code shows `+` when `isCollapsed` is `true`, which is correct. However, the variable name is misleading because `toggle()` returns whether the class was **added**, not whether the element **is** collapsed.

Actually, looking closer - **this code is correct** but uses confusing variable naming.

### **Bug 3: Multitrack Section Toggle Missing Icon Update**
The multitrack toggle (line 190 in HTML) uses `id="multitrackToggle"` but there's **no event listener** for it in main.js! Let me check the other module files.

Let me read the multitrack.js file to see if it initializes its own toggle:

